    "answer_id" : 28387757,
    "question_id" : 1327074,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Refer to <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20181219121911/http://forum.spring.io/forum/spring-projects/batch/76237-jdbccursoritemreader-with-named-parameters\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>\n<p>       </p>\n\n<p>write query with named parameter, use simple <code>ListPreparedStatementSetter</code> with all parameters in sequence. Just add below snippet to convert the query in traditional form based to available parameters,</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>ParsedSql parsedSql = NamedParameterUtils.parseSqlStatement(namedSql);\n\nList&lt;Integer&gt; parameters = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;();\nfor (A a : paramBeans)\n    parameters.add(a.getId());\n\nMapSqlParameterSource parameterSource = new MapSqlParameterSource();\nparameterSource.addValue(\"placeholder1\", parameters);\n// create SQL with ?'s\nString sql = NamedParameterUtils.substituteNamedParameters(parsedSql, parameterSource);     \nreturn sql;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
